        entry - The object to cast.
        clazz - The class of the U.

      • getCasted

        public static <U> U getCasted(Map<String,Object> map,
                              String key,
                              Class<U> clazz)
        Tries to get a key from a map as the target type. If it is a generic type, the captured types are not validated. Only the base object type is validated.
        Type Parameters:
        U - The type to get the object as.
        Parameters:
        map - The non-null map that possibly contains the key.
        key - The String key to get the value for from the map.
        clazz - The class of the U.
        Returns:
        The casted object of type U or null if the cast could not be done.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the map was null.

      • loadConfiguredClass

        public static <S> S loadConfiguredClass(String name,
                                        BulletConfig config)
        This method loads a given class name with the class name key and creates an instance of it by using a constructor that has a single argument for a BulletConfig. It then passes in the provided config and returns the constructed instance.
        Type Parameters:
        S - The type of the class.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of class name to load.
        config - The BulletConfig to use to create an instance of the class.
        Returns:
        A created instance of this class.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if there were issues creating an instance. It wraps the real exception.
